    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks these are good. maybe a bit too \"corporate\" though? i want to make sure i'm actually saying something meaningful. i feel like some people in town are getting kinda heated about all this DEI stuff lately, saying it's just performative. how can i write something that addresses the importance of it without sounding like i'm just following a trend?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To sound genuine, focus on *actions* rather than jargon. Instead of listing \"initiatives,\" talk about *how* you welcome people—like offering diverse seating or featuring local voices. A simple caption like, \"Our cafe is for *all* neighbors, every single day,\" speaks volumes about your intent without needing buzzwords. Authenticity comes from the feeling your customers get when they walk through your door.",
      "source": "target",
